# Jasmine — optional signing config for release builds. Copy to `.env` and fill in.
# `.env` is gitignored. Leave everything blank for unsigned local/test builds.
#
# Only `build_release.sh` (macOS) and `build_release.ps1` (Windows) read this.
# Dev builds (`build_dev.*`, `pnpm tauri dev`) never sign.

# ── macOS code signing (Developer ID) ────────────────────────────────────────
# From your keychain: `security find-identity -v -p codesigning`
APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: YOUR NAME (TEAMID)"

# ── macOS notarization — choose ONE of the two blocks below ───────────────────
# (A) App Store Connect API key (recommended):
APPLE_API_KEY=""           # Key ID, e.g. ABCD1234EF
APPLE_API_ISSUER=""        # Issuer UUID
APPLE_API_KEY_PATH=""      # path to AuthKey_XXXX.p8

# (B) Apple ID + app-specific password:
# APPLE_ID=""
# APPLE_PASSWORD=""         # app-specific password
# APPLE_TEAM_ID=""

# ── Windows code signing ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Windows signing is configured in src-tauri/tauri.conf.json
# (bundle.windows.certificateThumbprint or signCommand), not here.

# ── Cloud features (Gallery + telemetry) — OFFICIAL builds only ──────────────
# Vite inlines both vars into the bundle at build time. When EITHER is missing
# the cloud module short-circuits: Gallery button hidden, telemetry never sends,
# Jasmine runs as a pure local tool. Open-source self-builds simply leave these
# blank.
# (Official Jasmine builds set these; open-source self-builds leave them blank.)
VITE_JASMINE_API_BASE=""
VITE_JASMINE_API_KEY=""

# ── Releasing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# publish_release.sh / .ps1 currently publish installers to GitHub Releases only
# (via the `gh` CLI — `gh auth login`); no extra secrets needed here. The old
# auto-updater + R2/CDN upload path is removed until a Jasmine-owned update
# server exists; when it does, restore the updater signing key (ed25519) and the
# upload/manifest config (see git history).
